{
  "id": "java-501",
  "name": "Java 501 — Venus as MCP Server & Agent Integration",
  "description": "Complete guide to using Venus Notebooks as an MCP server with Claude, Copilot, Claude Code, and any agentic system",
  "created": "2026-03-14T15:00:00",
  "modified": "2026-03-14T20:20:38.7278214",
  "cells": [
    {
      "id": "j501-intro",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "# Java 501 — Venus as MCP Server & Agent Integration\n\nVenus Notebooks exposes a full **Model Context Protocol (MCP)** server, making every notebook, cell, and JShell session accessible to AI agents including **Claude Desktop**, **Claude Code**, **GitHub Copilot**, and any MCP-compatible agentic system.\n\n| Integration | Method | What agents can do |\n|---|---|---|\n| Claude Desktop | MCP over SSE | List/read/run notebooks, execute Java, run pipelines |\n| Claude Code | MCP over SSE | Same as above + build automation |\n| GitHub Copilot | REST API | Direct HTTP calls to all endpoints |\n| Any Agent | REST API or MCP | Full programmatic access |\n\n> **Base URL:** `http://localhost:8585`  \n> **MCP SSE:** `GET /api/mcp/sse`  \n> **MCP Messages:** `POST /api/mcp/messages`",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "anchor": null,
      "dependsOn": [],
      "pipelineSteps": []
