    {
      "id": "j501-h2-copilot",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "## 4. GitHub Copilot & VS Code Integration\n\nGitHub Copilot (and Copilot Chat) access Venus via the **REST API** directly. No MCP configuration needed — just instruct Copilot to use HTTP calls.\n\n### VS Code Extension Approach\n\nIn Copilot Chat, reference Venus endpoints:\n\n> *\"Call POST http://localhost:8585/api/shell/execute with sessionId='my-session' and code='var x = 42;' and show me the result\"*\n\n### Copilot Workspace / Agent Mode\n\nIn agent mode with tool access, Copilot can call:\n\n```http\n# List notebooks\nGET http://localhost:8585/api/notebooks\n\n# Run code\nPOST http://localhost:8585/api/shell/execute\nContent-Type: application/json\n{\"sessionId\": \"copilot-session\", \"code\": \"System.out.println(\\\"Hello from Copilot\\\");\"}\n\n# Create a notebook\nPOST http://localhost:8585/api/notebooks\nContent-Type: application/json\n{\"name\": \"Copilot Analysis\", \"description\": \"Generated by Copilot\"}\n```\n\n### MCP-Compatible Copilot Extensions\n\nIf your Copilot extension supports MCP, use the same SSE URL:\n```\nhttp://localhost:8585/api/mcp/sse\n```",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "anchor": null,
      "dependsOn": [],
      "pipelineSteps": []
    },
    {
      "id": "j501-h2-rest-api",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "## 5. REST API — Full Programmatic Access\n\nEvery Venus feature is available via REST API at `http://localhost:8585/api`. No authentication required for local use.\n\n### Core Endpoints\n\n#### Notebooks\n```http\nGET    /api/notebooks              → list all notebooks\nGET    /api/notebooks/{id}         → get notebook with all cells\nPOST   /api/notebooks              → create notebook {\"name\": \"...\"}\nPUT    /api/notebooks/{id}         → save full notebook JSON\nDELETE /api/notebooks/{id}         → delete notebook\n```\n\n#### Code Execution\n```http\nPOST /api/shell/execute            → run code in a session\nPOST /api/shell/execute-pipeline   → run pipeline cell\nPOST /api/shell/execute-with-deps  → run cell with dependencies\nPOST /api/shell/run-to-here        → run all cells up to target\nPOST /api/shell/{id}/restart       → restart session\nGET  /api/shell/sessions           → list active sessions\n```\n\n#### MCP\n```http\nGET  /api/mcp/sse                  → MCP SSE stream\nPOST /api/mcp/messages             → MCP JSON-RPC messages\n```\n\n#### AI / Claude\n```http\nPOST /api/llm/chat                 → chat with Claude\nPOST /api/llm/generate             → generate notebook from prompt\nPOST /api/llm/explain              → explain code\nPOST /api/llm/fix                  → fix code errors\n```",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "anchor": null,
      "dependsOn": [],
      "pipelineSteps": []
