    {
      "id": "j501-publish-via-mcp",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "//@ anchor: publish-via-mcp\n//@ description: Publish a new notebook via MCP from JShell\n\nimport java.net.http.*;\nimport java.net.URI;\n\nvar client = HttpClient.newHttpClient();\n\n// Step 1: Create a notebook via MCP\nvar createBody = \"{\\\"jsonrpc\\\":\\\"2.0\\\",\\\"id\\\":1,\\\"method\\\":\\\"tools/call\\\",\" +\n    \"\\\"params\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"venus_create_notebook\\\",\" +\n    \"\\\"arguments\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Agent Published Notebook\\\",\" +\n    \"\\\"description\\\":\\\"Created by an agent via MCP\\\",\" +\n    \"\\\"cells\\\":[\" +\n    \"{\\\"type\\\":\\\"MARKDOWN\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"# Agent Notebook\\\\n\\\\nThis notebook was published by an AI agent via MCP.\\\"},\" +\n    \"{\\\"type\\\":\\\"CODE\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"System.out.println(\\\\\\\"Hello from agent!\\\\\\\");\\\",\\\"anchor\\\":\\\"hello\\\"}\" +\n    \"]}}}\";\n\nvar req = HttpRequest.newBuilder()\n    .uri(URI.create(\"http://localhost:8585/api/mcp/messages\"))\n    .header(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    .POST(HttpRequest.BodyPublishers.ofString(createBody))\n    .build();\n\nvar resp = client.send(req, HttpResponse.BodyHandlers.ofString());\nSystem.out.println(\"Create notebook response:\");\nSystem.out.println(resp.body());",
      "output": "Create notebook response:\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":{\"content\":[{\"text\":\"Notebook created successfully.\\nID:    d6665688-ad9f-4457-aad1-1990b27d8e31\\nName:  Agent Published Notebook\\nCells: 3\",\"type\":\"text\"}]}}\r\n",
      "returnValue": "",
      "executed": true,
      "executionCount": 1,
      "error": "",
      "anchor": "publish-via-mcp",
      "dependsOn": [],
      "pipelineSteps": []
    },
    {
      "id": "j501-publish-via-rest",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "//@ anchor: publish-via-rest\n//@ description: Publish a notebook via REST API\n\nimport java.net.http.*;\nimport java.net.URI;\n\nvar client = HttpClient.newHttpClient();\n\n// Step 1: Create notebook\nvar createBody = \"{\\\"name\\\": \\\"REST Published Notebook\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Created via REST API\\\"}\";\nvar createReq = HttpRequest.newBuilder()\n    .uri(URI.create(\"http://localhost:8585/api/notebooks\"))\n    .header(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    .POST(HttpRequest.BodyPublishers.ofString(createBody))\n    .build();\nvar createResp = client.send(createReq, HttpResponse.BodyHandlers.ofString());\nSystem.out.println(\"Created: \" + createResp.body().substring(0, Math.min(200, createResp.body().length())));\n\n// Parse the ID (simple string scan)\nvar body = createResp.body();\nint idStart = body.indexOf(\"\\\"id\\\":\\\"\") + 6;\nint idEnd = body.indexOf(\"\\\"\", idStart);\nvar notebookId = body.substring(idStart, idEnd);\nSystem.out.println(\"New notebook ID: \" + notebookId);",
      "output": "Created: {\"id\":\"aa395226-1704-4e16-adf4-50716d180678\",\"name\":\"REST Published Notebook\",\"description\":\"\",\"created\":\"2026-03-14T20:16:23.6321375\",\"modified\":\"2026-03-14T20:16:23.6321375\",\"cells\":[{\"id\":\"9ada8582\r\nNew notebook ID: aa395226-1704-4e16-adf4-50716d180678\r\n",
      "returnValue": "",
      "executed": true,
      "executionCount": 2,
      "error": "",
      "anchor": "publish-via-rest",
      "dependsOn": [],
      "pipelineSteps": []
    },
    {
      "id": "j501-append-cell-demo",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "//@ anchor: append-cell-demo\n//@ depends: publish-via-rest\n//@ description: Append cells to the newly created notebook\n\nimport java.net.http.*;\nimport java.net.URI;\n\n// (notebookId from previous cell)\nvar client = HttpClient.newHttpClient();\n\n// Step 2: Append a code cell via MCP tool\nvar appendBody = \"{\\\"jsonrpc\\\":\\\"2.0\\\",\\\"id\\\":2,\\\"method\\\":\\\"tools/call\\\",\" +\n    \"\\\"params\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"venus_append_cell\\\",\" +\n    \"\\\"arguments\\\":{\\\"notebookId\\\":\\\"\" + notebookId + \"\\\",\" +\n    \"\\\"type\\\":\\\"CODE\\\",\" +\n    \"\\\"source\\\":\\\"var greeting = \\\\\\\"Hello from appended cell!\\\\\\\"; System.out.println(greeting);\\\",\" +\n    \"\\\"anchor\\\":\\\"greeting\\\",\" +\n    \"\\\"execute\\\":true,\" +\n    \"\\\"session\\\":\\\"demo-session\\\"}}}\";\n\nvar req = HttpRequest.newBuilder()\n    .uri(URI.create(\"http://localhost:8585/api/mcp/messages\"))\n    .header(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    .POST(HttpRequest.BodyPublishers.ofString(appendBody))\n    .build();\nvar resp = client.send(req, HttpResponse.BodyHandlers.ofString());\nSystem.out.println(\"Append cell result:\");\nSystem.out.println(resp.body());",
      "output": "Append cell result:\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":2,\"result\":{\"content\":[{\"text\":\"Cell appended to notebook 'REST Published Notebook'.\\nCell ID: cell-1773544584639\\nType:    CODE\\nTotal cells: 2\\n\\nExecution result:\\nStatus: SUCCESS\\nOutput:\\nHello from appended cell!\",\"type\":\"text\"}]}}\r\n",
      "returnValue": "",
      "executed": true,
      "executionCount": 3,
      "error": "",
      "anchor": "append-cell-demo",
      "dependsOn": [
        "publish-via-rest"
      ],
      "pipelineSteps": []
    },
    {
      "id": "j501-access-existing",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "## 6. Accessing Existing Notebooks & Packages via MCP\n\nAll existing notebooks are immediately accessible via MCP without any configuration.\n\n### Search for reusable code\n```json\n{\"method\": \"tools/call\", \"params\": {\"name\": \"venus_search_cells\",\n  \"arguments\": {\"query\": \"fibonacci\"}}}\n```\n\n### Load a module from another notebook\n```json\n{\"method\": \"tools/call\", \"params\": {\"name\": \"venus_load_module\",\n  \"arguments\": {\"notebookRef\": \"java-401/math-utils\", \"session\": \"my-session\"}}}\n```\n\n### Run a full pipeline\n```json\n{\"method\": \"tools/call\", \"params\": {\"name\": \"venus_run_pipeline\",\n  \"arguments\": {\"notebookId\": \"java-401\", \"cellId\": \"j401-etl-pipeline\",\n                \"session\": \"agent-etl-session\"}}}\n```\n\n### Package your notebooks as an API\nExpose any JShell function or pipeline to AI agents by:\n1. Give each reusable cell an `//@ anchor: name` annotation\n2. The anchor is immediately discoverable via `venus_search_cells`\n3. Any agent can load it into a session via `venus_load_module` and then call it via `venus_execute_code`",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
